badminton for Easter?

13:21.734 --> 13:23.902
I took it too far
this time, Cleveland,

13:23.904 --> 13:26.104
and now I realize
just how much I love her.

13:26.106 --> 13:30.308
The best thing I ever had
is gone forever.

13:30.310 --> 13:33.111
Dad, look at yourself
in the mirror.

13:33.113 --> 13:34.746
I'm fat.

13:34.748 --> 13:38.116
Look at us, a
couple of schmoes--

13:38.118 --> 13:40.318
one fat, one
heartbroke.

13:40.320 --> 13:42.754
You know what? Instead
of sitting here moping,

13:42.756 --> 13:44.589
get out there and
fight for Mom,

13:44.591 --> 13:46.291
and I'm gonna order
sliced tomatoes

13:46.293 --> 13:49.127
with my double cheeseburger
instead of fries--

13:49.129 --> 13:50.428
or maybe I'll get
the fries, too.

13:50.430 --> 13:52.263
I'll eat the tomatoes first,

13:52.265 --> 13:54.766
but I'll eat the fries
if I'm still hungry.

13:54.768 --> 13:57.335
I ain't never had to fight
for no woman in my life.

13:57.337 --> 13:58.436
That's what losers do.

13:58.438 --> 14:01.406
Hello, I did that.

14:02.641 --> 14:04.676
And I won the
love of my life.

14:04.678 --> 14:06.010
Think about it,

14:06.012 --> 14:07.445
and I'm going to
have a cheeseburger.

14:07.447 --> 14:09.280
And you know what?

14:09.282 --> 14:11.015
No tomatoes.

14:11.017 --> 14:15.854
Actually, avocado--
that's a good fat, like me.

14:16.789 --> 14:19.324
(children laughing)

14:19.326 --> 14:21.326
Don't mess
this up for me.

14:21.328 --> 14:23.294
I'm living my dream.

14:23.296 --> 14:26.197
Now, I've paid you both
handsomely to know your roles.

14:26.199 --> 14:29.334
Again, Roberta,
you are my wife Jane.

14:29.336 --> 14:31.169
Our son was an accident.

14:31.171 --> 14:32.704
You've talked yourself
into loving me

14:32.706 --> 14:34.472
because I'm a good provider.

14:34.474 --> 14:36.541
And that's why I drink.

14:36.543 --> 14:38.142
Perfect.

14:38.144 --> 14:40.311
Look, I'll be around
for the intros, photos,

14:40.313 --> 14:42.981
or when you need your son
to be in a sack race,

14:42.983 --> 14:44.349
but the rest
of the time,

14:44.351 --> 14:48.319
you can catch a brother
at the swangs!

14:48.321 --> 14:49.320
Perfect.

14:49.322 --> 14:51.322
Okay, showtime.

14:51.324 --> 14:54.192
Frank, you family-having
son of a gun.

14:54.194 --> 14:55.226
Nice to meet you.

14:55.228 --> 14:57.362
Well, hello there,
little guy.

14:57.364 --> 14:59.998
You look
just like your dad.

15:00.000 --> 15:01.833
Wow, that's a kick in the b...

15:01.835 --> 15:03.167
(chuckles)

15:03.169 --> 15:05.003
Run and play on
the swings, son.

15:05.005 --> 15:07.338
Swangs!

15:07.340 --> 15:10.742
(sighs)
Kids-- they
grow up so fast.

15:10.744 --> 15:12.577
So, why you keeping
Frank so late at work?

15:12.579 --> 15:14.279
You see he's
got a kid.

15:15.347 --> 15:17.248
Whoa, Jane.

15:17.250 --> 15:20.685
Don't you raise your fist
to me, you sad, little man.

15:20.687 --> 15:21.853
You know what?

15:21.855 --> 15:23.855
This is stupid dumb.
Screw this.

15:23.857 --> 15:28.826
I'm going to go make out with
my boyfriend in his mouth.

15:30.529 --> 15:32.196
(groans nervously)

15:32.198 --> 15:34.265
Jane!

15:37.102 --> 15:39.103
Wait!

15:39.105 --> 15:42.607
Why are they always fighting?

15:42.609 --> 15:43.875
(cries)

15:43.877 --> 15:46.978
Does anybody want
to buy me a toy?

15:53.285 --> 15:56.120
Mr. Oxnard, sir,
I-I want to apologize

15:56.122 --> 15:58.890
for that "situation"
at the picnic.

15:58.892 --> 16:00.425
Apologize for what?

16:00.427 --> 16:03.394
You handled that with
class and dignity.

16:03.396 --> 16:06.397
I've had marital problems with
my young, black wife, too.

16:06.399 --> 16:07.565
Like what?

16:07.567 --> 16:09.467
Oh, she didn't like
my brother watching us.

16:09.469 --> 16:11.469
Look, Lefkowitz, I'm
gonna get right to it.

16:11.471 --> 16:13.304
I'm going to give
you Myron's job.

16:13.306 --> 16:15.406
He'll figure out a way
to support his kids,

16:15.408 --> 16:16.808
even the one
in the chair.

16:16.810 --> 16:18.977
Mr. Oxnard, you're a prince.

16:18.979 --> 16:22.413
I've dreamed of an offer
like that my whole life,

16:22.415 --> 16:24.782
but I haven't been honest
with you.

16:24.784 --> 16:27.418
I'm not a high school graduate.

16:27.420 --> 16:29.954
Myron went to Harvard
and he's a total moron.

16:29.956 --> 16:33.791
Be that as it may, I can only
worry about Frank Lefkowitz,

16:33.793 --> 16:37.328
and Frank Lefkowitz
has got to get his GED.

16:37.330 --> 16:39.597
Well, Lefkowitz, there will
always be a desk for you

16:39.599 --> 16:41.432
here at McClennan
Reinsurers.

16:41.434 --> 16:42.600
Can I take it home?

16:42.602 --> 16:44.302
Huh, yes.

16:44.304 --> 16:46.971
Good-bye, Mr. Oxnard.

16:46.973 --> 16:50.375
♪

17:04.356 --> 17:06.457
Penn State?

17:06.459 --> 17:07.458
Yuck.

17:07.460 --> 17:08.960
Cleveland,
I need your help.

17:08.962 --> 17:10.461
Here, start with these.

17:10.463 --> 17:12.163
Also yuck.

17:12.165 --> 17:14.832
I'm gonna fight to get your mom
back from George Clinton.

17:14.834 --> 17:16.134
How?

17:16.136 --> 17:17.468
I'm gonna do
the only logical thing--

17:17.470 --> 17:19.470
start my own
'70s funk band.

17:19.472 --> 17:21.472
All I need now
is the band.

17:21.474 --> 17:24.142
You got some friends who might
be up for something crazy?

17:24.144 --> 17:25.143
Let me see.

17:25.145 --> 17:27.645
Dead, dead, dead,

17:27.647 --> 17:31.315
lost his thumbs, dead, dead.

17:31.317 --> 17:32.483
Wait a minute.

17:32.485 --> 17:34.819
Okay, one more,
one more.

17:34.821 --> 17:36.487
That was good.

17:36.489 --> 17:39.157
Now pretend I'm the Jostens man
and give me yearbook.

17:39.159 --> 17:41.225
Ah, forget it, here they come.

17:50.669 --> 17:53.571
Remember,
just scare 'em.

17:58.343 --> 18:00.578
(people screaming, Tim growling)

18:03.048 --> 18:04.849
He's good.

18:04.851 --> 18:07.518
ANNOUNCER:
Ladies and gentlemen, we regret

18:07.520 --> 18:10.521
to inform you that George
Clinton and the P-Funk All Stars

18:10.523 --> 18:13.391
have been mauled to death
by a bear.

18:13.393 --> 18:16.260
On a lighter note,
that bear plays guitar,

18:16.262 --> 18:17.695
so put your hands together

18:17.697 --> 18:21.165
for Freight Train
and the Palpitations.

18:23.869 --> 18:25.870
♪ <i>Ooh...</i> ♪

18:25.872 --> 18:26.904
Lavar?

18:26.906 --> 18:30.074
I want to send this out
to the only woman

18:30.076 --> 18:34.045
who's ever really mattered
in my life-- my wife

18:34.047 --> 18:36.547
Evelyn "Cookie" Brown.

18:36.549 --> 18:41.419
♪ <i>Ooh...</i> ♪
Cookie, I made mistakes,
I treated you wrong,

18:41.421 --> 18:43.221
but ever since you left me,

18:43.223 --> 18:47.458
I've been feeling sick, so bad.
♪ <i>Ooh...</i> ♪

18:47.460 --> 18:50.695
Everybody, gather around
in a circle because...

18:52.397 --> 18:55.099
♪ I'm feeling ookie, Cookie

18:55.101 --> 18:58.469
♪ <i>Ookie, Cookie</i> ♪
♪ Because I made such a mess

18:58.471 --> 19:02.306
♪ I'm eatin' my words now,
Cookie ♪

19:02.308 --> 19:05.143
♪ And they don't taste
the best ♪

19:05.145 --> 19:08.746
♪ Some people think
it's just a game ♪
♪ <i>Ooh...</i> ♪

19:08.748 --> 19:11.983
♪ But to me it means a lot
♪ <i>Quite a lot</i> ♪

19:11.985 --> 19:14.919
♪ My aim-- it might be shaky
♪ <i>Ooh...</i> ♪

19:14.921 --> 19:18.456
♪ But I'm gonna give it,
give it one last shot ♪

19:18.458 --> 19:21.492
♪ I'm feeling ookie, Cookie...

19:21.494 --> 19:24.795
I think Cookie Monster
put it best when he said,

19:24.797 --> 19:28.533
"'C' is for Cookie
and that's good enough for me."

19:29.434 --> 19:30.768
Yeah, those other women

19:30.770 --> 19:32.136
don't mean nothing.

19:32.138 --> 19:33.604
In fact, you know what?

19:33.606 --> 19:35.439
I'm gonna call them right now.

19:35.441 --> 19:38.609
Hello, Beatrice,
it's Freight Train.

19:38.611 --> 19:40.845
We're through.

19:40.847 --> 19:42.613
Hi, is this the Waffle House?

19:42.615 --> 19:44.448
Let me speak to Jalisa.

19:44.450 --> 19:46.517
Baby, I got to quit you.

19:46.519 --> 19:49.954
Hello, Maureen, we're done.

19:49.956 --> 19:52.623
Now give the phone to your mom.

19:52.625 --> 19:55.159
Hey, Doreen, you know
why your daughter's crying?

19:55.161 --> 19:56.694
Same goes for you.

19:56.696 --> 19:57.695
It's over.

19:57.697 --> 19:59.163
Why?

19:59.165 --> 20:00.765
I'll tell you why.

20:02.701 --> 20:06.637
♪ I'm feeling ookie, Cookie

20:06.639 --> 20:09.974
♪ <i>Ookie, Cookie</i> ♪
♪ I've been
a big old nasty jerk ♪

20:09.976 --> 20:12.843
♪ It'd be a big load off

20:12.845 --> 20:16.714
♪ <i>Big, huge load</i> ♪
♪ If we could just
make this work ♪

20:17.316 --> 20:18.649
♪ So

20:18.651 --> 20:22.553
ALL:
♪ Come on, Cookie.

20:25.857 --> 20:27.658
I'm sorry, Cookie.

20:27.660 --> 20:29.860
I love you and
your cooking

20:29.862 --> 20:32.730
and your tall-boy-
sized belly button

20:32.732 --> 20:34.832
and your
Libertarian politics

20:34.834 --> 20:36.667
and your ability
to drive a big rig

20:36.669 --> 20:38.536
a thousand miles without
changing your diaper.

20:38.538 --> 20:40.838
Oh, Lavar,
let's go home.

20:40.840 --> 20:42.006
You're gonna get
some cookies

20:42.008 --> 20:43.674
out of this cookie jar
tonight.

20:43.676 --> 20:45.509
Well, first you're gonna
run that cookie jar

20:45.511 --> 20:46.711
through the dishwasher.

20:46.713 --> 20:49.680
Oh, Lavar.

20:49.682 --> 20:51.015
♪ I'm feeling ookie, Cookie

20:51.017 --> 20:57.955
♪ Aah, Cookie!
